# Force LF line endings on commit regardless of contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
# Required by the catalog-sync drift safeguard: scripts/sync-critical-rules.ps1 and
# scripts/sync-critical-rules.sh both compute git hash-object of pattern-catalog.md
# and embed it into HIGH-TIER-SLUGS.md. Without consistent normalization, a Windows
# contributor with autocrlf=false would commit a CRLF blob while CI computes the
# LF blob hash - the pre-commit hook + CI parity check would block loudly.
# See panel-policy.md §"Catalog-edit + ack-sync invariant" for the full design.
* text=auto
